{title: Maple on the Hill}
{artist: Hank Locklin}
{composer: unknown}

[G]Here upon the quiet country village stood the [C]maple on the [G]hill
There I sat with my [A7]Geneva long [D7]ago
[G]When the stars were shining brightly we could [C]hear the whippoor[G]will
As we sat beneath the [D7]maple on the [G]hill
We would sing love songs together when the [C]birds had gone to [G]rest
And we'd listened to the [A7]murmur of the [D7]leaves
